## Error Handling & Edge Cases

### Edge Case Matrix

| Scenario | Detection | Handling | Response |
|----------|-----------|----------|----------|
| **Invalid email format** | Regex validation | Reject immediately | 400 Bad Request |
| **Empty recipient list** | Pre-validation | Reject immediately | 400 Bad Request |
| **Subject too long (>200 chars)** | Length check | Truncate with warning | 200 OK with warning |
| **Body too large (>1MB)** | Size check | Reject immediately | 413 Payload Too Large |
| **Too many recipients (>100)** | Count check | Reject immediately | 400 Bad Request |
| **Attachment too large (>25MB)** | Size check | Reject immediately | 413 Payload Too Large |
| **Too many attachments (>10)** | Count check | Reject immediately | 400 Bad Request |
| **Invalid attachment encoding** | Base64 validation | Reject immediately | 400 Bad Request |
| **Blacklisted domain** | Domain check | Reject immediately | 403 Forbidden |
| **Not whitelisted domain** | Domain check | Reject immediately | 403 Forbidden |
| **Rate limit exceeded** | Token bucket | Reject with retry-after | 429 Too Many Requests |
| **SMTP connection timeout** | Timeout detection | Retry 3x, then failover | 500 or 202 (async) |
| **SMTP authentication failure** | Auth error | Fail fast, alert ops | 500 Internal Server Error |
| **Circuit breaker open** | Circuit state | Fail fast, use backup | 503 Service Unavailable |
| **Thread pool full** | Queue check | Reject or caller-runs | 503 Service Unavailable |
| **Malicious HTML content** | Sanitization | Clean HTML, log warning | 200 OK (sanitized) |
| **Missing API key** | Header check | Reject immediately | 401 Unauthorized |
| **Invalid API key** | Key validation | Reject immediately | 401 Unauthorized |
| **Duplicate request ID** | Idempotency check | Return cached response | 200 OK (cached) |
| **Network partition** | Connection error | Retry, then DLQ | 500 or 202 (async) |
| **SMTP server down** | Connection refused | Switch to backup | 200 OK (backup used) |

