### Retry Strategy

```java
@Retryable(
    value = {MailException.class, MessagingException.class},
    maxAttempts = 3,
    backoff = @Backoff(
        delay = 2000,
        multiplier = 2,
        maxDelay = 10000
    ),
    exclude = {MailAuthenticationException.class}
)
public void sendEmail(MimeMessage message) {
    // Send logic
}
```

**Retry Timeline:**
- Attempt 1: Immediate (t=0s)
- Attempt 2: After 2s (t=2s)
- Attempt 3: After 4s (t=6s)
- If all fail → Dead Letter Queue

### Dead Letter Queue Processing

```java
@Scheduled(fixedDelay = 300000) // Every 5 minutes
public void processDLQ() {
    List<FailedNotification> failed = dlqRepository.findRetryable();
    
    for (FailedNotification notification : failed) {
        if (notification.getRetryCount() < 5) {
            try {
                retryNotification(notification);
                dlqRepository.delete(notification);
            } catch (Exception e) {
                notification.incrementRetryCount();
                dlqRepository.save(notification);
            }
        } else {
            // Max retries exceeded - alert operations
            alertOps(notification);
            dlqRepository.markAsPermanentFailure(notification);
        }
    }
}
```

